{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "29", "m": "05", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "07", "M": "43", "S": "53"}}, "news": [{"title": "Top 11 listed developers\u2019 pre-sales rise 18% to \u20b91.48 lakh crore in FY26: Anarock", "para": "The combined pre-sales of 11 listed real estate developers increased 18% year-on-year to \u20b91.48 lakh crore in FY26, according to Anarock. Developers with higher exposure to premium and luxury housing, along with those expanding beyond their home markets, recorded stronger growth during the year.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/real-estate-boom-top-developers-pre-sales-surge-18-in-fy26/131384795?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-47178/131384795.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Online plan approval system falters, Goa's town planning department still leans on offline route", "para": "Goa's town planning department has processed over 6,000 technical clearances but only a handful of construction licenses online since 2020. The Building Plan Approval Management System, intended for transparency, sees limited use. Data reveals delays in approvals, with offline methods seemingly preferred. While the system now covers more projects, experts suggest wider adoption for better business ease.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/technology/goas-online-building-approval-system-struggles-as-town-planning-department-sticks-to-old-habits/131381057?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-33776/131381057.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "technology"}, {"title": "Mumbai developer accuses former partner of cheating him out of \u20b911.51 crore", "para": "A Mumbai developer has accused his former partner of cheating him out of Rs 11.51 crore by allegedly concealing the prior sale of 19 flats in a Bandra East slum rehabilitation project. The Economic Offences Wing has registered an FIR for cheating, forgery, and breach of trust against the accused, who is alleged to have diverted sale proceeds.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/mumbai-developer-accuses-ex-partner-of-1151-crore-fraud-in-slum-rehab-project/131380938?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-18216/131380938.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}]}